#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:2
msgid ""
"**Rolisteam** is a **free virtual table software**. Pen and paper Role "
"playing games are traditionnaly made around table. Virtual table software "
"seems to be the right solution to overcome real life difficulties."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:4
msgid ""
"It is also multiplatform software (Windows, MacOS and Linux). Download it "
"here : "
"[http://www.rolisteam.org/download](http://www.rolisteam.org/download) \n"
"then install it on your computer. **Rolisteam** provides many features to "
"live a better game experience (such as : maps, images, dice roller, "
"charactersheet, background music). "
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:6
msgid ""
"**Rolisteam** is available in several languages: english, french, spanish, "
"german, portuguese, hungrian, dutch, romanian and partially in turkish."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:8
msgid ""
"Now, Let's explain how to use **Rolisteam**. Many screenshots illustrate "
"this tutorial to make it funnier and easier to understand."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:10
msgid "#I – Start and Settings"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:12
msgid ""
"On start, Rolisteam appears and above it there is the *connection panel*. "
"This panel allows you to add and set connection profile. You must set "
"correct values to ensure the connection establishement. \n"
"\"Player\" profile requires definition of player's character as well. \n"
"This panel may store several connection profile."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:14
msgid "![images]({static}/images/tuto/04_connexion_mj_en.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:16
msgid ""
"Change the default profile or create another one. We recommand to set a "
"meaningful name. It makes it easier.  \n"
"For example, I use to play as GM on Wednesday and as player on Monday, "
"names of my profiles are: Game on Monday, Game on Wednesday."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:18
msgid "There are four connection mode in **Rolisteam**: "
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:22
msgid "Host and GM"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:25
msgid "Client and GM"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:28
msgid "Host and Player"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:31
msgid "Client and Player"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:35
msgid ""
"**GMs** (Game Masters) have more control and power over **Rolisteam** than "
"**players**. They can add maps or images. They control background music and "
"many more stuff."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:37
msgid ""
"The differences between **host** and **client** may appear not really "
"obvious. Hosting the game means that all game players must connect to you.\n"
"If the hosting **Rolisteam** is closed, everybody will be disconnected from "
"the game."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:39
msgid "Game Master or Player"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:40
msgid ""
"The *Player* area is dedicated to describe yourself. You have to pick up "
"(nick)name (it will appears to other players) and select a color. For a "
"better game experience, it is better than all players chose a very "
"different color."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:42
msgid ""
"The last thing is a checkbox \"**I am the game master**\". Check it only if "
"you are the GM, obviously. "
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:44
msgid ""
"If you are a player, the connection panel allows you to describe your "
"character thinks of the \"**Character**\" zone.\n"
"It is displayed only when you are not the **game master**. "
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:46
msgid ""
"You must set the character name, color and avatar. It is recommanded to use "
"square image as avatar (for better good looking on vectorial maps)."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:48
msgid "Host or Client"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:49
msgid "Host"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:50
msgid ""
"If you host the game, the server must be on your side. You don't need to "
"set an address. You must pick up a port and check \"**Host the game**\".\n"
"When you are confident about your connection profile, you must click on "
"\"**Connect**\". If everything goes right, the connection profile dialog "
"disappears and let you access to the main application window."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:52
msgid ""
"In the notification area (Top right corner), there is a reminder of "
"connection information you should give to other game participants. "
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:54
msgid "![images]({static}/images/tuto/14_notification_zone_en.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:56
msgid ""
"As you can see, the address in our case is *194.250.98.228*, and the port "
"is *6661*. By default, **Rolisteam** use the port *6660*. You can change it "
"as you want but please avoid port number used by another service.  "
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:58
msgid ""
"Chose the host carefully, bandwidth and stability are the main two "
"criteria.   \n"
"Game experience will be better. DSL line is enough and do the job "
"perfectly. Keep in mind, the host must stay until the end of game. Everyone "
"will be disconnected if the host is off. "
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:60
msgid "Client"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:61
msgid ""
"If you connect as client, you need an address and port number to join the "
"game. Rolisteam can access IP address  (example: *194.250.98.228*), or "
"domain namee (rolisteam.org, games.foo.com). The host must give you those "
"information."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:63
msgid "Uncheck the \"host the game\" checkbox. "
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:65
msgid ""
"Then you are all set. Click on **Connection**. If it goes right, the "
"connection dialog disappears and you have acces to the application."
msgstr ""

