#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:210
msgid "Dice Alias (or how to make your life easier)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:211
msgid ""
"Complex system may require complex and long command. The alias system is "
"dedicated to help in this case. It provides a way to simplify commands. "
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:213
msgid ""
"Let see this example: !6d10e10k3  \n"
"This command implements the Roll & Keep system from «Legend of the 5 "
"rings».\n"
"It is painful to write the command every time. A shorter command will be "
"appreciated and more pratical.\n"
"To do so, **Rolisteam** provides aliases. To write a clever alias, you have "
"to think about few points.\n"
"First, identify the changing part of the system.  \n"
"Does the dice number change ?  \n"
"Does the difficulty threshold change ?  \n"
"etc.  "
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:215
msgid ""
"Those are the questions you should ask yourself.   \n"
"In our case, the rolled dice and kept dice change.\n"
"So, you can define an alias in the preferences dialogs."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:217
msgid ""
"Alias: K => d10e10k  \n"
"how to use it:   "
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:221
msgid "!6K3 = !6d10e10k3  "
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:224
msgid "!8K4 = !8d10e10k4  "
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/tmpz6m6l9ck.md:228
msgid ""
"There are two kinds of alias:\n"
"Alias by replace (like the previous example)\n"
"Alias by regular expression.\n"
"Please, take a look at the "
"[documentation](http://wiki.rolisteam.org/index.php/en:preferences#) to get "
"more information about aliases."
msgstr ""

